summary.name: Budget Forecasts
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing budget forecasts for various years.

goals.question: What is the trend of budget forecasts over the years?
goals.visualization: line chart of value against forecastYear
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to identify if there is an increasing or decreasing trend in budget forecasts over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of budget forecasts for each year?
goals.visualization: box plot of value against budgetYear
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to identify if there are any outliers or if the budget forecasts are consistent across the years.

goals.question: What is the average budget forecast for each year?
goals.visualization: bar chart of mean value against budgetYear
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to identify the years with the highest and lowest budget forecasts.

goals.question: What is the correlation between budgetYear and forecastYear?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of budgetYear against forecastYear
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to identify if there is any correlation between the budget year and the forecast year.

goals.question: What is the distribution of budget forecasts for each forecast year?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help to identify if there are any patterns or trends in the distribution of budget forecasts for each forecast year.

code:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['forecastYear'], data['value'])
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Budget Forecast Value (% of GDP)')
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget forecasts over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Budget Forecast'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='value', by='budgetYear', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of budget forecasts for each year?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Budget Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Forecasted Budget Value (% of GDP)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    ax = data_grouped.plot.bar(x='budgetYear', y='value', legend=False)
    plt.title('What is the average budget forecast for each year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Forecast Value')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['budgetYear'], data['forecastYear'])
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between budgetYear and forecastYear?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year

    plt.hist(data['value'], bins=20, alpha=0.75, label='Budget Forecasts', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['value'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['value'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Forecasted Budget Value as a Percentage of GDP')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budget forecasts for each forecast year?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
